content.description: Start matched on low ledge. Make your way up to the higher ledge with some fun moves. Traverse to the crack on some good holds, then up the crack and top out over the bulge. Variety of nice holds, potential kneebar rest, toping out is probably the crux. Fairly good land zone. Could be a good warm up for some of the more difficult problems around it. Loose rocks on the top out so look out below!
content.location: Same approach to the scumalong boulder (aka dab boulder), once you find the dab boulder just take the trail to the wall directly behind it. This is the problem to the right of the mini roof feature.

content.description: Starts on some good holds under the roof left of Look out below.  Maybe cam your foot in the hole to give yourself access to the top. Make your way up the left side of the roof on some big holds with some big moves and a nice mantle at the end.
content.location: Starts on the low jugs left of the mini roof feature on the wall behind the scumalong boulder.

content.description: Chill little spot with some problems.
